HEADWORD: Take-up
<hw>Take"-up`</hw> <pr>(t⟦amac⟧k"⟦ucr⟧p`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>That which takes up or tightens; specifically, a
device in a sewing machine for drawing up the slack thread as the needle
rises, in completing a stitch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Taking</ent>⟦br⟧
